    <!-- About Section -->
    <section class="section" id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">What is Control Engineering?</h2>
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Control Engineering is a multidisciplinary branch of engineering that applies control theory to design systems with desired behaviors. It focuses on the modeling of dynamic systems and the design of controllers that will cause these systems to behave in the desired manner. These controllers manipulate the inputs to a system to obtain the desired effect on the output of the system.</p>
                    <p>As a control engineer, you'll work on designing systems that maintain stability, accuracy, and efficiency across various applications—from simple thermostats to complex aircraft flight control systems, industrial automation, and robotics. You'll apply mathematical principles and engineering techniques to ensure systems perform reliably and predictably under changing conditions.</p>
                    <p>This field combines elements of electrical engineering, mechanical engineering, computer science, and mathematics to create solutions that are essential in modern technology. Control systems are ubiquitous in our daily lives, from cruise control in cars to industrial robots and spacecraft guidance systems.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Areas Section -->
    <section class="section bg-dark" id="key-areas">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--light-text);">Key Areas of Study</h2>
            <p class="section-intro" style="color: var(--light-text);">Control Engineering encompasses several specialized areas that form the foundation of modern control systems:</p>
            
            <div class="cards-grid three-columns">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-project-diagram"></i> Classical Control Theory</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of control systems through transfer functions, frequency domain analysis, and time domain analysis. This includes PID controllers, root locus techniques, and stability analysis using methods like Routh-Hurwitz criteria.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Transfer Function Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Laplace transforms, block diagrams, signal flow graphs</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Stability Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Routh-Hurwitz criteria, Nyquist stability criterion</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Controller Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">PID controllers, lead-lag compensators</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-vector-square"></i> Modern Control Theory</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of control systems using state-space representation, which allows for the analysis and design of multiple-input, multiple-output (MIMO) systems. This includes state feedback, observers, and optimal control strategies.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">State-Space Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">State variables, controllability, observability</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Optimal Control</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">LQR, LQG, H-infinity control</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">State Estimation</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Observers, Kalman filters</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-random"></i> Nonlinear Control</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of control systems with nonlinear dynamics, which are more realistic representations of real-world systems. This includes techniques like Lyapunov stability analysis, feedback linearization, and sliding mode control.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Nonlinear System Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Phase portraits, limit cycles, bifurcations</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Lyapunov Stability</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Stability analysis of nonlinear systems</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Advanced Control Techniques</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Feedback linearization, sliding mode control</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cards-grid three-columns" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-brain"></i> Intelligent Control</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The application of artificial intelligence techniques to control systems. This includes fuzzy logic controllers, neural networks, and genetic algorithms for adaptive and learning control systems.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Fuzzy Logic Control</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Fuzzy sets, linguistic variables, inference systems</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Neural Network Control</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Learning algorithms, adaptive control</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Evolutionary Algorithms</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Genetic algorithms, particle swarm optimization</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-microchip"></i> Digital Control Systems</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The implementation of control algorithms using digital computers or microcontrollers. This includes discrete-time system analysis, digital controller design, and real-time implementation considerations.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Discrete-Time Systems</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Z-transforms, difference equations, sampling</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Digital Controller Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Digital PID, state feedback, deadbeat control</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Real-Time Implementation</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Embedded systems, timing considerations</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-industry"></i> Process Control</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The application of control theory to industrial processes such as chemical plants, oil refineries, and manufacturing systems. This includes process modeling, PID tuning, and advanced process control strategies.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Process Modeling</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">First-principles models, empirical models</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">PID Tuning Methods</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Ziegler-Nichols, Cohen-Coon, IMC tuning</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Advanced Process Control</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Model predictive control, cascade control</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

